object.script:
wasEmit = false emitLength = 0 notEmitLength = 0
lastEmitLength = 0 lastTicksBetweenSignals = -1
lastValues = {} function onTick() emit = input.getBool(1)
averageLastValues = input.getBool(2)
if emit then emitLength = emitLength + 1 else notEmitLength = notEmitLength + 1 end
if not emit and wasEmit then lastEmitLength = emitLength emitLength = 0 end
if emit and not wasEmit then lastTicksBetweenSignals = notEmitLength + 1 -- +1 b table.insert(lastValues, 1, lastTicksBetweenSignals) while #lastValues > 10 do table.remove(lastValues, 11) end notEmitLength = 0 end
wasEmit = emit
if averageLastValues then total = 0 count = 0 for li, l in ipairs(lastValues) do if l > 0 then total = total + l count = count + 1 end end output.setNumber(1, total/count) else output.setNumber(1, lastTicksBetweenSignals) end end

object.n: My Static ID (must be unique and between 1 and 60 when NO Automatic ID Assignment is used)

object.script:
function onTick() battery = input.getNumber(1) timeBetweenEmits = input.getNumber(2) myId = input.getNumber(3) hasSendInLastFewSeconds = input.getBool(1) end
function onDraw() S=screen SW = S.getWidth() SH = S.getHeight() screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawTextBox(0,0,SW,9, "Batt " .. math.floor(battery*100) .. "%", 0,0)
screen.drawTextBox(0,12,SW,7,math.floor(timeBetweenEmits) .. " ticks", 0,0) screen.drawText(0,20,"between emits")
if myId > 0 then screen.drawTextBox(0,35,SW,14,"My ID: " .. math.floor(myId), 0,0) else screen.drawTextBox(0,35,SW,14,"No ID, press button", 0,0) end
if hasSendInLastFewSeconds then screen.setColor(0, 120, 0) screen.drawTextBox(0,52,SW,7,"Connected", 0,0) else screen.setColor(120, 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(0,52,SW,7,"Disconnected", 0,0) end end
